race.comment: GYMKHANA (5) finished out of the money two starts back then he got a long way back and was beaten 3.5 lengths when ninth over 1600m at Cranbourne 2.5 weeks ago. Finds a more suitable contest back in 56 grade and can find winning form. OCEAN SYMPHONY (2) accounted for a maiden field over 1600m at Cranbourne last start when fresh from a break and while this is tougher and he's drawn well, he'll have come on fitness-wise. WINTER GRACE (12) was a nice maiden winner two back and will find this more suitable than last start in town. EXBANOISE (7) found only better in a 0-62 at Cranbourne last start and seems to appreciate the gap between runs that he has coming into this. Drawn well and gets in nicely after the claim.
